- VSCode Version: 1.13.1
- OS Version: Windows 8.1 64-bit

I have the following type definitions:
```ts
interface DataType {
    key: string,
}
type PlatformType = 'hiperreg' | 'uC';
type PlatformDTO = PlatformHiperreg | PlatformMicroController;

interface PlatformBase extends DataType {
    type: PlatformType,
    name: string,
    supportsVersions: boolean,
}

interface PlatformHiperreg extends PlatformBase {
    type: 'hiperreg',
}

interface PlatformMicroController extends PlatformBase {
    type: 'uC',
    brand: 'avr' | 'pic',
    model: string,
}
```

and then I use it as follows:
```ts
const platforms: PlatformDTO[] = [
    {
        type: 'hiperreg',
        key: 'hiperreg',
        name: 'HiperReg',
        supportsVersions: true,
    },
    {
        type: 'uC',
        key: 'avr-atmega8',
        name: 'ATmega8',
        brand: 'avr',
        model: 'ATmega8',
        supportsVersions: false,
    },
]
```

What happens is then when I'm entering entry with `type: 'uC'` the autocomplete doesn't suggest fields `brand` and `model` which exists only on type `PlatformMicroController` which is distinguished by field `type`.
